    "Hereditary spherocytosis is caused by defects in the red cell membrane cytoskeleton (spectrin, ankyrin, band 3, or protein 4.2), so cells lose surface area, become spherical, and are trapped and destroyed in the spleen. The smear shows spherocytes with an elevated MCHC, the direct Coombs test is negative (distinguishing it from autoimmune hemolysis), osmotic fragility is increased, and splenectomy is curative in severe cases.",
