    "Von Gierke disease (GSD type I) results from deficient glucose-6-phosphatase, the enzyme that releases free glucose from the liver. Without it, the liver cannot complete gluconeogenesis or glycogenolysis, causing severe fasting hypoglycemia, lactic acidosis, hepatomegaly, hyperuricemia (G6P shunted to the pentose pathway), and hyperlipidemia. Management centers on frequent feeds and cornstarch to maintain glucose.",
