    "OTC deficiency is the most common urea cycle disorder and the only X-linked one. The enzyme block backs up carbamoyl phosphate into the pyrimidine pathway, so urine orotic acid rises while ammonia accumulates, causing neonatal encephalopathy. The key discriminators: CPS1 deficiency causes hyperammonemia WITHOUT elevated orotic acid, and hereditary orotic aciduria causes elevated orotic acid WITH megaloblastic anemia but normal ammonia.",
