    'Phenylketonuria',
    "Every can of diet soda carries the warning \"Phenylketonurics: Contains Phenylalanine\" because aspartame is broken down into that amino acid. The disease this warning protects against also presents in an unscreened infant with intellectual disability, eczema, a musty body odor, and unusually fair hair and skin, with markedly elevated plasma phenylalanine. Which deficient enzyme explains both the soda warning and this phenotype?",
